The paper discusses the use of perceptual aspects in video coding, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM) and computer vision (cs.CV). It also mentions the use of alternative approaches and optimization for metrics, which could fall under information theory (cs.IT). The focus on codec design and evaluation further supports the likelihood of cs.MM being the most relevant sub-category.
